Attached garages/carports site planning

• Attached garages must comply with same setbacks as main dwelling.

Note: Uncovered spaces must be located
beyond the required frontyard and beyond
the first 10' of the street-side yard.

visual_elements.description: Figure 33 is a top-down site plan diagram illustrating three different scenarios (A, B, C) for attached garages and parking on residential lots. It shows property lines, setbacks, dwelling footprints, and parking locations. A key on the right explains the symbology used.
visual_elements.location: Middle and bottom of the page

visual_elements.description: Sub-diagram 'A' shows an 'Interior lot example' with a main dwelling. A '1-car attached' garage is located on the left side of the dwelling. An 'Uncovered space' for a second vehicle is shown in the 'Interior-side yard' behind the 'Distance of front setback' line. The diagram labels the 'Front yard' and 'Rear yard'.

Sub-diagram 'B' shows an 'Interior lot example' with a main dwelling. A '1-car attached' garage is located in front of the main dwelling. An 'Uncovered space' for a second vehicle is shown in the driveway, directly in front of the attached garage. The diagram labels 'Front yard', 'Rear yard', and 'Interior-side yard'.

Sub-diagram 'C' shows a 'Corner lot example' with a main dwelling. A '2-car attached' garage is located on the right side of the dwelling, adjacent to the 'Street-side yard'. A '10'' dimension is indicated as a setback from the street-side lot line, creating a 'No-parking area'. The diagram labels 'Front yard', 'Rear yard', and 'Street-side yard'.

A 'Key' or legend that defines the graphical elements used in the diagrams. It includes:
- Solid black line: Curb
- Dashed black line: Lot line
- Tiled gray rectangle: Sidewalk
- Long dashed line: Required setbacks
- Light gray area with dashed border: Buildable area
- Medium gray solid area: Dwelling
- Dark gray/black solid area: Parking structure
- Hatched area: No-parking area
- Icon of a car: Uncovered space
A small icon of a top-down view of a car, used to represent an 'Uncovered space' in the diagrams and the key.
visual_elements.location: Within diagrams A, B and the Key

visual_elements.description: A grey rectangular box with white text, labeled 'Note', providing a specific regulation about uncovered spaces.
